race.comment: VERBIL (1) registered his fourth win from just nine starts when he led all the way and easily accounted for a similar quality field here at this trip last start. Had only ever won first-up prior to that which shows how well he is going. Carries some serious weight this evening but can get the job done again. APOLLO MISSION (2) has been safely held at his last two appearances, both in tougher races than this. Gets back and draws the fence so he will need luck at some stage but a much better run looks on the cards. ECLAIR ENCORE (3) worked home well to finish fourth to the in-form Meridiana over the mile at Newcastle (metro) recently. Genuine filly whose form is good enough to test this field. FIFTYFIVECHEVY (5) showed pace but weakened late when resuming over 1500m at Rosehill last start. Loves this trip and has won second-up before so don't take him lightly. CLIMB THE LADDER (12) hasn't won for a while but is worth throwing in the exotics.
